title: Sports Minute: Here is the latest Florida sports from The AP
text:
COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) - Kelvin Taylor rushed for 99 yards and two first-quarter touchdowns and No. 11 Florida defeated Missouri 21-3 on Saturday night. The Gators amassed 337 yards and possessed the ball for 37:53, converting 23 first downs as quarterback Will Grier completed 20 of 33 passes for 208 yards in his fifth start.
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) - Dalvin Cook ran for 222 yards and three touchdowns, the last a 23-yarder with 6:44 remaining, to help No. 12 Florida State hold off Miami 29-24 on Saturday night. Florida State won despite Miami's Brad Kaaya throwing for 405 yards and three touchdowns.
BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) - Driphus Jackson led the game-winning 83-yard drive, and the Rice defense stopped Florida Atlantic in the final minute to clinch a 27-26 comeback win in Boca Raton on Saturday. In Tampa, Marlon Mack rushed 179 yards and a pair of second-half touchdowns Saturday to help South Florida end a three-game losing streak with a 45-24 victory over Syracuse.
SUNRISE, Fla. (AP) - Jaromir Jagr and Reilly Smith each scored twice and Vincent Trocheck had a goal and three assists as the Florida Panthers dominated their season opener 7-1 against the Philadelphia Flyers on Saturday night. Elsewhere, Steven Stamkos scored his first goal of the season Saturday, helping the Tampa Bay Lightning defeat the Buffalo Sabres 4-1.
